    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_5]",
      "span_text": "Here, we demonstrate that a variant of soluble VEGF receptor-1 (sVEGFRv-1), a truncated form of sFLT-1 packaged in a recombinant adeno-associated virus 2 (rAAV2) delivery vehicle, may serve as the basis for developing gene therapy modalities against wet AMD. rAAV2 vectors are particularly attractive for this purpose due to their ability to elicit long-term transgene expression and transduce non-dividing cells, in addition to being non-pathogenic by nature."
    }
